        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 19 at 3:00PM EDT until June 19 at 3:30PM EDT by NWS Baltimore MD/Washington DC</headline>
        <description>At 300 PM EDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Sperryville to 10 miles east of Big Meadows to 6
miles northwest of Madison to near Afton, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Damaging winds will cause some trees and large branches to
fall. This could injure those outdoors, as well as damage
homes and vehicles. Roadways may become blocked by downed
trees. Localized power outages are possible. Unsecured
light objects may become projectiles.

Locations impacted include...
Culpeper, Warrenton, Madison, Sperryville, Hume, Big Meadows,
Marshall, Brightwood, Opal, Flint Hill, Washington, Castleton,
Catalpa, Brandy Station, Hackleys Crossroads, Haywood, Amissville,
Jeffersonton, Cresthill, and Syria.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
